---
import LegalLayout from '@/layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
const year = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<LegalLayout title="Terms of Service | BUILD3R" description="BUILD3R Terms of Service">
  <div class="space-y-12 pb-20">
    <section class="mx-auto w-full max-w-4xl px-6 pt-20">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-primary-500">Terms</p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-600">Last updated: {year}</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto w-full max-w-4xl space-y-6 px-6 text-sm text-slate-600">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Engagements</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Services are delivered according to the scope, timeline, and pricing agreed in your proposal. Additional work outside of scope requires a change order and updated estimate.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Payment</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Productized engagements typically require a 50% deposit to reserve the sprint window, with the balance due at delivery. Care plans are billed monthly in advance.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Intellectual property</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Upon final payment, you own the work product delivered. Build3r retains the right to reuse underlying frameworks and tools that are not specific to your business.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Confidentiality</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          We treat all non-public information you share as confidential and only use it to deliver the agreed services.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Liability</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, our liability is limited to the fees paid in the twelve months preceding the claim. We are not liable for indirect or consequential damages.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</LegalLayout>
